	url = {http://arxiv.org/abs/1310.6630},
	abstract = {We provide a set of exact solutions in field theory of scalar fields with Z2 symmetry that involve Jacobi elliptic functions. These solutions have the interesting property to provide massive waves even if one starts from a massless equation. We analyze them classically providing also exact solutions to the corresponding equations for the Green functions needed to completely solve them in a strong coupling limit. This is accomplished using a functional expansion into powers of the current. It is shown that the spontaneous breaking of the Z2 symmetry is due to the existence of a zero mode that persists also in the case of the Higgs mechanism. In this latter case, the zero mode seems to play a role similar to the Goldstone boson in the breaking of a continuous symmetry and so, it should be important at lower momenta as a long range excitation.},
